00:56:03,280 --> 00:56:05,920
Oh! It's a clean pen.
It's a very good pen.


894
00:56:08,560 --> 00:56:11,680
Well, I thought that was impressive.
Very. Very good.


895
00:56:11,680 --> 00:56:16,280
I certainly was impressed.
My word! Helen, what are you doing
on this field?


896
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:18,640
You should be up there, competing!


897
00:56:18,640 --> 00:56:23,680
I think it's fair to say
I had a very good teacher who
chipped in now and again.


898
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:27,080
OK! To be honest, we could have
left Spot to his own devices.


899
00:56:27,080 --> 00:56:29,520
He was quite happy out there
on his own. Brilliant.


900
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:34,120
He thoroughly enjoyed it. Look,
the sheep are sticking around. They
want to know who's won.


901
00:56:34,120 --> 00:56:35,560
Gus, what's the result?


902
00:56:35,560 --> 00:56:39,400
Really, you were level pegging,
but on a technicality you got it


903
00:56:39,400 --> 00:56:44,320
because Helen went and moved
from the post, from the pen
when you set the dog off.


904
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:46,960
What?!
Yep, unfortunately for you...


905
00:56:46,960 --> 00:56:50,680
That's a made-up rule,
I didn't even know about it!


906
00:56:50,680 --> 00:56:53,600
Thanks ever so much. That's
all we've got time for this week.


907
00:56:53,600 --> 00:56:55,400
Con-gratu-lations!


908
00:56:55,400 --> 00:56:59,320
Next week we're going to be
in the Mawddach estuary in Wales


909
00:56:59,320 --> 00:57:04,160
and we'll be revealing your
favourite entry of the Countryfile
photographic competition.


910
00:57:04,160 --> 00:57:07,680
But, from Helen's neck of the woods,
it's come by for now. See you.


911
00:57:07,680 --> 00:57:10,200
You looked so cool until that gag.


912
00:57:10,200 --> 00:57:12,560
It's undermined the victory!



